# Podlesnoye, Sterlitamaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Podlesnoye () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative centre of Podlesnensky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 376 as of 2010. There are 3 streets.
Geography
Podlesnoye is located 29&nbsp;km north of Sterlitamak (the district's administrative centre) by road. Ishparsovo is the nearest rural locality.
